WorkItem.Description:
I have the following TypeScript code:

import path = module('path');
import stringx = module('stringx');

Where path is the NodeJS module, and stringx.ts is a file in the same directory.

The following Javascript is generated:

var path = require('path')
var stringx = require("./stringx")

Although it is valid and works, the second module() statement uses double quotes instead of the single quotes I had originally. JSHint doesn't like this when using the quotmark: true option.
